DATE FORMATTING & CASTING
--------------------------
2025   -  08  - 20    18    :  55  :   45
yyyy   -  MM  - DD    HH    :  mm  :   ss
Year    Month   Day   Hour    Minutes  seconds

ISO Format
-----------
2025   -  08  - 20 
yyyy   -  MM  - DD

US - Format
----------
08  -   20  - 2025
MM      DD  - YYYY

eu - Format
----------
20  -   08  - 2025
DD  -   MM  - YYYY

FORMAT   --> syntax  FORMAT(value, format,culture)  default culture en-US
  when using HH won't AM/PM Its 24 HOURS FORMAT
  hh  it will show in 12 hour format with AM/PM ... AM/PM format is tt
  
SELECT
CreationTime,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'MM-dd-yyyy') USformat,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'dd-MM-yyyy') EUformat,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'MM') MM,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'MMM') MMM,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'MMMM') MMMM,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'dd') dd,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'ddd') ddd,
FORMAT(CreationTime,'dddd') dddd,
OrderID
FROM
SalesDB.Sales.Orders

SELECT
CreationTime,
'Day ' + format(CreationTime,'ddd MMM')+' Q'+DATENAME(quarter,CreationTime)+FORMAT(CreationTime,' yyyy hh:mm:ss tt') as format1,
OrderID
FROM
SalesDB.Sales.Orders

